{
  "doc_id": "17536",
  "text": "In support of the cognitive deficit hypothesis, children with ADHD show maturation delays in the prefrontal cortex [CITATION_1] . Among children with ADHD, those with poorer executive functioning, cognitive fluency, and working memory have larger explicitly measured PIB in the social (although not in the behavioral) domain [CITATION_2] . Some evidence suggests that as children with ADHD become older, their self-perceptions of their behavioral conduct (although not their social acceptance) become more aligned with adult-informant ratings, resulting in reductions in PIB [CITATION_3] , although importantly other research finds PIB to persist among adults with ADHD (e.g., [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
